
# Learning:
-> Recall the different types of loops.  
-> Understanding what loops are and how they work.  
-> Finding the differences between do-while loops, while loops and for loops.  
-> Writing code that logs all numbers from 1 to 1000.  
-> Writing code that keeps reading input data until an empty string is passed.  
-> Understanding what loop iterations are and how to skip some of them.  
-> Understanding the break keyword in the context of loops.  
-> When given code that contains loops, being able to determine if I should use a for, while or do-while loop.  
-> What are loops, types of loops - entry controlled and exit controlled.  
-> While loop, break statement.  
-> For loop, for loop components - initializer, condition, iterator.  
-> Continue operator  

